Creating a Skip Variable 
This next query sets a skip variable. In your language and environment of choice you can then iterate through a loop, query to get 1000 pools each time,
and continually adjust skip by 1000 until all pool responses are returned.
Check out this example  from our interface for poolDayData that does something similar .
Note: This query will not work in the graph explorer and more resembles the structure of a query you'd pass to some graphql middleware like Apollo.
query pools( $skip: Int!) {
    pools(
      first: 1000
      skip: $skip
      orderDirection: asc
    ) {
      id
      sqrtPrice
      token0 {
        id
      }

