Subscribing to Events  
During the lifecycle of the swap widget, most of the events you will need are available on the web3 provider . For example,
the below snippet shows how to listen for events when the wallet account changes or a new wallet connects. You can see
more event examples in the MetaMask  docs.
// Subscribe to messages
interface  ProviderMessage  {
  type: string;
  data: unknown ;
}
ethereum .on(
  'message' ,
  handler: (message: ProviderMessage ) => void
);
